cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with Non-Rigid Structure from Motion (NRSfM), which is a subfield of computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses modifications to an existing algorithm to improve its performance, which involves machine learning techniques. 
3. cs.GR (Graphics): NRSfM is also related to 3D graphics and animation, as it deals with estimating the 3D structure of a deforming object from 2D images. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper involves processing and analyzing multimedia data, specifically image sequences. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics): NRSfM has applications in robotics, as it can be used to estimate the 3D structure of a deforming object in real-time.
